commit.message:
Fix rioutil -a

Not sure how this was working before but it certainly isn't working now. This
commit fixes an issue with riotil -a that prevents the command from working as
expected.

Signed-off-by: Nathan Hjelm <hjelmn@cs.unm.edu>

bump version to 1.5.4

Signed-off-by: Nathan Hjelm <hjelmn@me.com>

rioutil: fix support for memory target selection

This commit fixes two bugs:

 - Fix a bug in processing filenames that do not include a '/'.

 - Fix a bug where all files were uploaded to memory unit 0.

 - Update the -a option to upload all files between the -a and the
   next option.

Signed-off-by: Nathan Hjelm <hjelmn@me.com>

librioutil: update file headers with correct license

Signed-off-by: Nathan Hjelm <hjelmn@mac.com>

add missing COPYING.LESSER file

Signed-off-by: Nathan Hjelm <hjelmn@mac.com>

Cleanup repo and warnings

This commit removes a number of warnings and removes the builtin
version of getopt. Most systems have a working copy of getopt_long at
this point.

Complete the switch to new logging functions.  The rio_log() function is replaced by 
debug(), warning(), and error().  The new logging functions don't depend on the rio struct, 
and the debug level is now stored globally.  Logging levels are defined in riolog.h

The output should still look the same as before.
